content: Can't believe I bought this. I see no pictures of every component lol

This is a great resource, so why the 1 star? There should be an option within the app that allows you to scroll through pre-jump and the other materials in their entirety without having to cycle through flash cards. As much as the flashcards are helpful, I found it frustrating not having the option of just pulling up pre-jump and reading through it all at once. I asked for a refund from the app store within 5 minutes of having this app, however if this is fixed I will definitely get it again.

Overall, the app is pretty helpful. My main issue is with the audio. If you touch the screen, or leave the app, or even let the screen rotate at all, the audio starts over. It would be nice to see the ability to put the audio on a loop so you can set it to listen to continually in the background while doing something else. Also, it would be nice to have individual items of prejump recorded so you could easily choose specific sections of prejump to listen to.

Let's keep it real.

content: Best Jumpmaster app hands down. Updated the weapons case to include the Modular Airborne Weapons Case. Wish it had a voice recorder for you to playback when studying for Pre-Jump and a stop watch that alerted you when you should be done with Combat and Hollywood jumpers... (2 minute and 1:30 second marks). Maybe even a 1 minute warning. This way when you did your ghost jumpers or even if a buddy got their hands on a chute you could see how fast smooth really is. Fantastic app for new and current Jumpmaster!

This app is a great tool to study for, refresh, or just learn about jumpmaster school (Benning 507th) and static line parachuting operations. However, the app does not provide enough timely updates to keep up with the ever changing Army, or specifically with the 507th. New versions of pre-jump are constantly updated and published on the Benning or 82nd JM site, but this app lags behind by several versions, so more often than not, you will be studying an outdated version with this app. Otherwise, great app!
replyContent: Hi Jeffrey, we're getting caught up.  The pace of change will not continue like this.  This is mostly related to the new TC.  Prior to this there were about 2 years with little change.  Things will settle down shortly.
